            "id": "4539296",
            "title": "The UK's GDP expands in November,",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li id=\"description\">The UK economy expanded by 0.3% M/M in November 2025, rebounding from a 0.1% contraction in October and outperforming market expectations of 0.1% growth.</li>\n<li id=\"description\">Real GDP per head is estimated to have shown no growth in the latest quarter and is up 0.9% compared with the same quarter a year ago. Monthly GDP increased to 1.40% Y/Y in November from 1.1% in October.<span> </span>\n</li>\n<li>The value of goods imports decreased by £0.6B (1.1%) in November, with a fall in imports from non-EU countries partially offset by a rise in imports from the EU.</li>\n<li>The goods trade balance in the UK increased to -£23710M in November from -£24170M in October of 2025.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
