            "id": "4539277",
            "title": "Trump holds off on critical minerals tariffs",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">U.S. President Donald Trump said Wednesday he is holding off—for now—on imposing <span>tariffs on imports of critical minerals</span>, opting instead to direct his administration to seek supplies from international partners.</p>\n<p><span>In a presidential proclamation released Wednesday, Trump</span> instructed U.S. Trade Representative Jamieson Greer and Commerce Secretary Howard Lutnick to \"jointly negotiate agreements with trading partners to address the threatened impairment of national security with respect to imports of processed critical minerals and their derivative products from any country.\"</p>\n<p>He said the talks should explore price floors for critical minerals, a long-standing goal of Western miners and policymakers. Finance ministers from the G7 and other major economies, including Australia, discussed the idea during meetings in Washington earlier this week.</p>\n<p>If negotiations fail, Trump said he would consider setting minimum import prices for critical minerals or \"may take other measures,\" without elaborating.</p>\n<p>The announcement follows a months-long review assessing whether foreign shipments pose a threat to U.S. national security. In April 2025, Trump signed an executive order launching an investigation into the national security risks stemming from U.S. reliance on imported, processed critical minerals and related products.</p>\n<p>China, which produces more than half of the 54 minerals deemed critical by the U.S. Geological Survey, has curtailed exports over the past year amid trade tensions with Washington and remains a key global refiner of these materials.</p>\n<p>Back in October, Trump<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4505661-trump-signs-agreement-on-critical-minerals-with-australia\" target=\"_blank\" title=\" signed \"> signed </a>an agreement with visiting Australian Prime Minister Albanese to boost cooperation in accessing critical minerals and rare earths as the U.S. seeks to reduce reliance on Chinese supply chains.</p>\n<p>Australia, which holds the world's fourth-largest deposits of rare earths, has attempted to position itself as a viable alternative to China for supplies, and Lynas Rare Earths (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LYSCF\" title=\"Lynas Rare Earths Limited\">LYSCF</a>) (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LYSDY\" title=\"Lynas Rare Earths Limited\">LYSDY</a>) in Australia is the only current producer of heavy rare earths outside China.</p>\n<p>The Trump administration has also secured critical minerals agreements with Saudi Arabia, Malaysia, Thailand, Japan, and others. In addition, the administration has taken equity stakes in several critical minerals companies—spending more than $1 billion over the past year—to counter China’s dominance in raw materials, including investments in MP Materials (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MP\" title=\"MP Materials Corp.\">MP</a></span></span>) and Lithium Americas (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LAC\" title=\"Lithium Americas Corp.\">LAC</a></span></span>).</p>\n<p>Commodities reacted to the announcement, with the silver spot price (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XAGUSD:CUR\" title=\"Silver Spot Price\">XAGUSD:CUR</a>) down nearly <span>4% </span>at $89.75 an ounce after hitting an all-time peak of US$93.75 earlier on Wednesday. Gold spot price (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XAUUSD:CUR\" title=\"Gold Spot Price\">XAUUSD:CUR</a>) also fell 0.4% to $4,608.67 an ounce.</p>\n<p>Other relevant companies to watch, including USA Rare Earth (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/USAR\" title=\"USA Rare Earth, Inc.\">USAR</a>), Critical Metals (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CRML\" title=\"Critical Metals Corp.\">CRML</a>), Oklo (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OKLO\" title=\"Oklo Inc.\">OKLO</a>), Westwater Resources (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WWR\" title=\"Westwater Resources, Inc.\">WWR</a>), United States Antimony (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UAMY\" title=\"United States Antimony Corporation\">UAMY</a>), Eos Energy Enterprises (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EOSE\" title=\"Eos Energy Enterprises, Inc.\">EOSE</a>), NioCorp Developments (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NB\" title=\"NioCorp Developments Ltd.\">NB</a>), NuScale Power (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SMR\" title=\"NuScale Power Corporation\">SMR</a>), American Battery Technology (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ABAT\" title=\"American Battery Technology Company\">ABAT</a>), Uranium Energy (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UEC\" title=\"Uranium Energy Corp.\">UEC</a>), Northern Dynasty Minerals (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NAK\" title=\"Northern Dynasty Minerals Ltd.\">NAK</a>), Energy Fuels (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UUUU\" title=\"Energy Fuels Inc.\">UUUU</a>), Nano Nuclear Energy (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NNE\" title=\"NANO Nuclear Energy Inc.\">NNE</a>), Ramaco Resources (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/METC\" title=\"Ramaco Resources, Inc.\">METC</a>), Cameco (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CCJ\" title=\"Cameco Corporation\">CCJ</a>), Denison Mines (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DNN\" title=\"Denison Mines Corp.\">DNN</a>), Perpetua Resources (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PPTA\" title=\"Perpetua Resources Corp.\">PPTA</a>), Nouveau Monde Graphite (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NMG\" title=\"Nouveau Monde Graphite Inc.\">NMG</a>), Trilogy Metals (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TMQ\" title=\"Trilogy Metals Inc.\">TMQ</a>), and TMC the metals company (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TMC\" title=\"TMC the metals company Inc.\">TMC</a>).</p>\n<p>ETFs: (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XME\" title=\"State Street® SPDR® S&amp;P® Metals &amp; Mining ETF\">XME</a></span></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/REMX\" title=\"VanEck Rare Earth and Strategic Metals ETF\">REMX</a></span></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SETM\" title=\"Sprott Critical Materials ETF\">SETM</a></span></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LIT\" title=\"Global X Lithium &amp; Battery Tech ETF\">LIT</a></span></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/LITP\" title=\"Sprott Lithium Miners ETF\">LITP</a></span></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BATT\" title=\"Amplify Lithium &amp; Battery Technology ETF\">BATT</a></span></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COPP\" title=\"Sprott Copper Miners ETF\">COPP</a></span></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NLR\" title=\"VanEck Uranium and Nuclear ETF\">NLR</a></span></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/URA\" title=\"Global X Uranium ETF\">URA</a></span></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/URNM\" title=\"Sprott Uranium Miners ETF\">URNM</a></span></span></span>)</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
