            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\"> </p>\n<p><span>Toyota Industries (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TYIDY\" title=\"Toyota Industries Corporation\">TYIDY</a></span>) (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TYIDF\" title=\"Toyota Industries Corporation\">TYIDF</a></span>) share price surged on the Japanese stock exchange to a record high after Toyota Motors (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TM\" title=\"Toyota Motor Corporation\">TM</a></span>) announced a sweetened buyout offer by over 15% to over $35B.</span></p>\n<p><span>Toyota Motor <a href=\"https://www.release.tdnet.info/inbs/ek/140120260114534016.pdf\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">raised the buyout offer</a><span> for the group company to 18,800 yen per share, from 16,300 yen apiece announced in June last year.</span></span></p>\n<p><span>Toyota Industries, the original founder of Toyota Motor in the 1930s, produces forklifts, engines, and auto parts. </span></p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
